features: Hide and Squeak Eggs: An adorable and educational addition to your Easter egg basket, this squeak toy contains 6 colorful squeaking Easter eggs kids can play with
Crack Them Open: These interactive Easter gifts for toddlers feature shells that crack open to reveal adorable colorful chicks for kids to marvel at while they play
Interactive Toys: Press down gently on the colored chicks' heads to hear them chirp, creating a delightful auditory choir that keeps kids exploring and giggling
Child Development Toy: These educational toys help kids improve recognition of colors and shapes as they sort each egg into its own special base in the box, creating the ultimate sensory toy play
Perfect Gift: These plastic easter eggs are perfect for your kids easter baskets, holiday stockings, or birthdays with their compact size, adorable colors, and cute chick theme
body.description: Chirp! Chirp! These are not your ordinary chicken eggs you find at the grocery store! When your kids crack open the shells, they'll find a rainbow surprise with egg-straw special colorful chicks! Let your kids laugh and play with these colorful chicks while learning important skills. Match each chick with their specific shape and color in their carton for a fun way to help kids learn. Press down gently on their heads to hear them Cheep! Kids will love making them chirp and squeak, and you'll love the simplicity of these fun toys. This baby toy does not require batteries. These compact boy and girl toys are perfect gifts for holidays, fitting in perfectly as Easter toys in Easter baskets for kids. They are great travel toys too or store them neatly in their carton for on-the-go fun. These colorful plastic eggs with adorable chicks will help toddlers ages 18 months and up develop their fine motor skills while providing hours of entertainment with their delightful design.

reviews.reviewText: These eggs are cute, colorful, and educational! My loves to say “open” and open the carton. He also loves putting the tops onto the eggs.The eggs themselves squeak when you push down on them. Each egg has a shape at the bottom, which corresponds to a slot in the carton case. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great integration in speech therapy!
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these for my son after encountering them at his speech therapy. My 2 year old absolutely loves them and really makes practicing speech fun. I love that it covers facial expressions, color matching/identification and shapes! I appreciate that you have to work a little to find the right spot for each egg and getting the tops on the eggs, not too hard, but enough to make it a challenge to where they are working on dexterity and also truly need to know what shape fits where. It's a very engaging toy and the cute squeak sound they make is probably my 2 year olds favorite part. They're also very durable, the case included! Buy these asap!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2017
reviews.reviewText: This is an early Easter gift to my 7 month old son and he LOVES them! I figured with his age he would be too young but nope. He loves to dump out the eggs and pick up and teeth on the shells and rolling them around. He gives the biggest grin when he spots these and even goes for them during tummy time. He loves to knock the shells off the egg by banging them which is really easy to do. The eggs are super cute also and it's helping his dexterity and coordination to pick the egg up which is harder then the shell but he has done it a few times already. He loves for me to push down on the chicks to hear them peep. I love the mechanism in how it peeps by pushing against the screw inside. It's a very solid toy and looks safe. I have had fun playing with then also. They all have different ccolos and the shell has a face with cute facial emotions on every shell and there emotions colors match the egg color. It's also a shape sorter. It's great for matching, learning emotions and shape sorting and dumping out. Ohhh and of course teething and learning colors. This is definitely a toy that will grow with him as toddler and the price is great. My baby loves these during tummy time chasing the eggs on the floor. If you have a younger baby around 6 months all the way into toddler/small children stages they wilk love these adorable eggs. They are great year round. Anything that makes my baby happy makes me happy and these are fun to play with. The chicks are inside the top shell but the chicks aren't removable from the bottom shell, they are made into the bottom shell. These are super cute and definitely woth the $10 cost because of the versatility of this toy and it doesn't take up much much, it's a great price. Everyone needs these!. :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2012
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect toy for all ages
reviews.reviewText: My almost 17 month old got these eggs for Christmas. As soon as she opened them, her two older sisters dropped their toys and swarmed over to their baby sister and her new gift... Play food is so much fun for kids, and these haven't disappointed yet.Our eggs' pieces fit perfectly, they squeak a great squeak accordingly, and the carton closes snugly. There are absolutely no problems with our product, which relieved me because I read so many disparaging reviews. The squeak, by the way, isn't a loud thing. It's reminiscent of old fashioned squeak toys that just peep. And there are no choking hazards with this set. Very durable, and the paint hasn't come off at all (and we have a major chewer in this house!)I like the fact that the eggs' expressions aren't colored because that makes it more of a challenge for the older two kids (ages 6 and 3). The point is to match the shell's face to the yolk's face. The expressions differ slightly to greatly, so it's fun to have them study the faces. (The 6 year old has no problem; the 3 year old is at a perfect age for this part of the toy.) The baby likes to put the pieces together and apart and press down to squeak them. The sorting and matching is a bit above her. And all the eggs' "cracks" are cut the same, so all the tops and bottoms fit each other. The bottom of the carton has a shape depression in each hole, and each bottom shell has a corresponding key shape that fits into it. That's the frustrating part for the baby, but she is getting the hang of it with the help of a big sister;)All in all, this is a great toy for your child to grow with. For infants/young toddlers, it works on motor skills. For older toddlers/preschoolers, the sorting and matching part is perfect. For older kids, the eggs are great for pretend play with cooking and kitchens. Take the chance and get this toy. If you do get a defective one, Amazon is great about refunding!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Fun and Educational Toy for Little Ones!
reviews.reviewText: The TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs have been an absolute hit in our household! As a parent, finding toys that are both entertaining and educational is always a priority, and this toy perfectly fits the bill.The adorable design of the eggs, each with a unique facial expression, has proven to be both entertaining and stimulating for my child. The vibrant colors are visually appealing and have captured my child's attention, keeping them entertained for extended periods.The interactive squeaking feature adds an extra element of surprise and excitement, delighting my little one every time they press the eggs. Furthermore, the build quality of the eggs is excellent, and they are durable enough to withstand the inevitable drops and knocks from active play. The size is just right for little hands, making it easy for my child to grasp and manipulate the eggs independently.Overall, the TOMY Toomies Hide and Squeak Eggs have proven to be an essential addition to our collection of educational toys. Their interactive nature, educational benefits, and sturdy build make them a must-have for any parent looking to foster their child's early learning and development.Highly recommended for endless hours of educational fun!
